webwork-tex.statement:
If C is the curve given by \(\mathbf{r} \left( t \right) = \left( 1 + 5 \sin t
\right) \mathbf{i} + \left( 1 + 5 \sin^{2} t \right) \mathbf{j} + \left( 1 + 5
\sin^{3} t \right) \mathbf{k}\), \(0 \leq t \leq \frac{\pi}{2}\) and {\bf  F
} is the radial vector field \(\mathbf{F} \left( x, y, z \right) = x
\mathbf{i} + y \mathbf{j} + z \mathbf{k}\), compute the work done by {\bf  F
} on a particle moving along C.
  \par 
\mbox{\parbox[t]{20ex}{\hrulefill}}
